    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.13" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ALLEN TUPPER TRUE
                        <lb/>
                    DENVER, COLORADO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 5. 23.</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>My Dear Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am delighted with your suggestion re: the use of one of my paintings in connection with the Indian Wars. When the form of the book is decided upon let me know and anything I have is at your disposal. I would like to stuff in a <unclear>pen</unclear >and ink sketch &#8212; just Indian characterization &#8212; no illustration of text or anything of that sort &#8212; a <unclear>pen</unclear> and ink sketch here and there&#8212; make them now and then from now on until publication for my own satisfaction and as "thumb nail" studies for bigger work. <unclear>Praugroyu</unclear> used to do a lot of this sort of thing and it keeps a fellow keyed up.</p>
                    
                <p>You know I used to earn my cheese at illustration and have done work for all the good magazines except <unclear>Howden</unclear>. Spent 6 years with Howard Pyle who was our premier illustrator <unclear>Royalips</unclear>, <unclear>pay etc</unclear> dont figure so far as I'm concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Hastily,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Allen True</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note place="left margin" type="authorial"><unclear>Am</unclear> working hard these days on The "Indian Memories" 16 panels 1300 sq. ft. of murrals<sic>murals</sic> for the finest bank in the city. Expect is to be my "Clefdoover". <hi rend="caps">AT</hi>.</note>
               
            </div1>
        </body>
        
